<i>♪ Pressure</i> by Orion Sun playing ♪

24:56.038 --> 24:58.123
♪ vocalizing ♪

24:58.123 --> 25:01.293
♪

25:01.293 --> 25:02.503
[Paige chuckles]

25:03.253 --> 25:05.631
<i>♪ Low, got me running on E ♪</i>

25:05.631 --> 25:07.049
<i>♪ All this pressure on me ♪</i>

25:07.049 --> 25:10.511
<i>♪ Got me wishing I was six feet deep ♪</i>

25:10.511 --> 25:12.304
<i>♪ In the yard ♪</i>

25:12.304 --> 25:15.891
<i>♪ Somebody checking
for me in the streets ♪</i>

25:15.891 --> 25:20.604
So, sometimes we look at people

25:21.313 --> 25:23.398
and we think that we see them.

25:23.398 --> 25:27.152
But... trauma is on the inside.

25:27.152 --> 25:30.322
Trauma is like the rings inside a tree

25:30.322 --> 25:32.199
where if you open us up,
you could say like,

25:32.199 --> 25:34.409
oh, that's where the fire happened.

25:34.409 --> 25:37.496
Or over there,
that is where the drought was.

25:37.496 --> 25:41.208
And you don't ever
really get "past" your trauma

25:41.834 --> 25:44.044
because your trauma is always inside you

25:44.044 --> 25:47.214
just like that precious little child
is always inside of you

25:47.214 --> 25:48.924
trying to work it through,

25:48.924 --> 25:51.093
and they need you.

25:51.093 --> 25:54.429
That work of hearing them,
that is what allows us

25:54.429 --> 25:57.558
to carry our trauma forward
in a totally new way,

25:57.558 --> 26:00.519
in a way that connects us
and doesn't separate us

26:00.519 --> 26:01.937
from the people that we love.

26:03.772 --> 26:05.899
Or even from really nice people

26:06.859 --> 26:09.444
because everybody deserves nice people.

26:10.571 --> 26:14.199
You deserve nice people.

26:15.784 --> 26:16.994
Me, too.

26:30.424 --> 26:31.300
I'm Bumpy.

26:31.967 --> 26:32.968
Edwin.

26:32.968 --> 26:35.512
It's just a car, right, nothing else?

26:37.014 --> 26:38.015
Don't get pulled over.

